description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you a skilled registered nurse with excellent interpersonal skills and sound clinical assessment skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have the confidence to work alone, putting the patient at the heart of what you do; and to get involved with the multi-disciplinary team?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you passionate about supporting patients holistically to leave the hospital earlier, and avoid repeat admission?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you answered yes, we’ve got the perfect role for you!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want a dynamic and passionate nurse committed to providing holistic care in a broad range of community settings including patients own homes, to join our self-managing team, working in Parkwood and Wigmore.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team has professional autonomy and responsibility; working in supporting and empowering each other to deliver the highest standards in person centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this is you, we look forward to welcoming you to our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So what else?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is your chance to join a progressive and innovative service in a social enterprise that is patient and staff focused - you’ll even have the opportunity to become an MCH shareholder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We encourage staff to get involved in exploring new ways of working and service development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We’ll provide well established, in-service training, one to one supervision, and appraisals with regular support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll be able to develop your skills in a friendly and supportive team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So what are you waiting for? We can’t wait to hear from you, and look forward to receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The small print&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informal visits can be arranged on request.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will always appoint the best person for the job, but applications are particularly welcome from candidates from BAME groups which are underrepresented in our service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will offer you the choice of two pension schemes; the NHS Pension scheme and the scottish widows group pension scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 1 December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name  Kechi Okoye&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Neighbourhood Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email addressnkechinyelu.okoye@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number07775632835&lt;/p&gt;
